# English copy: no Oxford comma

In **English** user-facing strings (UI, `readme.txt`, comments meant for admins, marketing copy, error messages, doc aimed at English readers):

- **Do not** use the **Oxford comma** (serial comma) before the final conjunction in lists of three or more items.
- **Prefer:** “quotes, submissions and profiles”
- **Avoid:** “quotes, submissions**,** and profiles”

Apply this to new or edited English text in **`wpis-plugin`**, **`wpis-theme`** and workspace docs. **French** and other languages follow their own typographic rules (do not impose this rule on non-English copy).
